### Before reporting an issue

- [X] I have searched existing issues
- [X] I have reproduced the issue with the latest release

### Area

authentication

### Describe the bug

I have a custom EventListenerProvider which instanciate a FreeMarkerEmailTemplateProvider() to send a email with keycloak.

My implementation works well with the keycloak version 21.0.1. but no longer works in  21.1.x.

When I debug Keycloak, I see that there is no realm in the context of the KeycloakSession given to EventListenerProviderFactory in order to instanciate my EventListenerProvider.

I have this error : 
Cannot invoke "org.keycloak.models.RealmModel.getEmailTheme()" because the return value of "org.keycloak.models.KeycloakContext.getRealm()" is null

Example of my code : 
```
public class BlockLoginEventListenerProviderFactory extends EventListenerProviderFactory {

    @Override
    public BlockLoginEventListenerProvider create(KeycloakSession keycloakSession) {
        return new BlockLoginEventListenerProvider(keycloakSession);
    }

    @Override
    public String getId() {
        return "gzl-block-login";
    }
}
```

```
public class BlockLoginEventListenerProvider extends EventListenerProvider {

   KeycloakSession keycloakSession;

    public BlockLoginEventListenerProvider(KeycloakSession keycloakSession) {
       this.keycloakSession = keycloakSession;
    }

    @Override
    public void onEvent(Event event) {
          MyUserModelAdapter myUserModelAdapter = (MyUserModelAdapter) this.getKeycloakSession().users().getUserById(keycloakSession.getContext().getRealm(), event.getUserId());
          ...
          try {
              // Create email template
              EmailTemplateProvider emailTemplateProvider = new FreeMarkerEmailTemplateProvider(this.keycloakSession)
                      .setRealm(keycloakSession.getContext().getRealm())
                      .setUser(myUserModelAdapter);
              // Send email
              emailTemplateProvider.send("xxx", "email-blocked.ftl", attributes);
         } catch (EmailException e) {
              log.warn("Mail not sent");
         }
    }
}
```

### Version

21.1.0 & 21.1.1

### Expected behavior

When I log in throught account client (https:/xxx/auth/realms/myRealm/account/), i want to send an email to notify the user if it account is disabled. For this I use an specific implementation of EventListenerProvider and EventListenerProviderFactory.

Example of KeycloakSession provided to create an instance of EventListenerProvider when it works : 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47445051/235863696-c515fb3b-7856-42b1-8a87-67652be6dd17.png)

### Actual behavior

Unable to instanciate a FreeMarkerEmailTemplateProvider to send an email in the onEvent() method of my custom EventListenerProvider implementation.

The KeycloakSession provided in the create() method of the factory doesn't contains the RealmModel. A realm is required to retrieve the email templates.

Example of bad KeycloakSession provided to create an instance of EventListenerProvider : 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47445051/235863867-077b3ed0-ec4d-4870-9a8f-6c8e00e3847c.png)

Note that this create() method is called 3 times during the connection attempt. The first two times, the KeycloakSession provided contains the realm but the third time it is no longer the case


### How to Reproduce?

Implement an EventListenerProvider and an EventListenerProviderFactory which instanciate a FreeMarkerEmailTemplateProvider in the onEvent() method. Try to log in to an user account (/realms/myRealm/account). An exception should be thrown.

